<UserControl
    x:Class="D4LootBench.App.Views.Help.BuildGuideImportTopic"
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
    xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
    xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
    mc:Ignorable="d">

    <FlowDocumentScrollViewer>
        <FlowDocument FontFamily="Segoe UI" FontSize="13" PagePadding="20,16">

            <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Margin="0,0,0,12">
                Build Guide Import
            </Paragraph>

            <Paragraph>
                Build Guide Import generates a BiS (Best in Slot) loot filter directly from a gear
                section copied from a build guide. Paste the gear table, click
                <Bold>Import Filter</Bold>, and D4LootBench produces a ready-to-use filter with one
                rule per gear slot — no manual rule building required.
            </Paragraph>

            <Paragraph FontSize="14" FontWeight="SemiBold" Margin="0,12,0,6">
                Supported sites
            </Paragraph>

            <List Margin="8,4,0,12">
                <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Mobalytics</Bold> — copy the gear section from a Mobalytics build guide</Paragraph></ListItem>
                <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Maxroll</Bold> — copy the gear section from a Maxroll build guide</Paragraph></ListItem>
                <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Icy Veins</Bold> — copy the gear table from an Icy Veins build guide</Paragraph></ListItem>
            </List>

            <Paragraph FontSize="14" FontWeight="SemiBold" Margin="0,8,0,6">
                How to use it
            </Paragraph>

            <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="8,4,0,12">
                <ListItem>
                    <Paragraph>
                        Open a build guide on Mobalytics, Maxroll, or Icy Veins and navigate to the
                        gear / Best in Slot section.
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
                <ListItem>
                    <Paragraph>
                        Select the gear table or gear list and copy it to the clipboard
                        (<Bold>Ctrl+C</Bold>).
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
                <ListItem>
                    <Paragraph>
                        In D4LootBench, click <Bold>Import from Build Guide</Bold> in the toolbar
                        (the book icon next to Paste Code).
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
                <ListItem>
                    <Paragraph>
                        Paste the copied text into the text area (<Bold>Ctrl+V</Bold>). The format
                        is detected automatically — or select it manually from the dropdown if
                        auto-detect fails.
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
                <ListItem>
                    <Paragraph>
                        Click <Bold>Import Filter</Bold>. Review any warnings, then confirm to
                        replace your current filter.
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
            </List>

            <Paragraph FontSize="14" FontWeight="SemiBold" Margin="0,8,0,6">
                What gets generated
            </Paragraph>

            <Paragraph>
                The importer creates one rule per gear slot, plus combined rules for unique items
                and talisman sets when the guide specifies them:
            </Paragraph>

            <List Margin="8,4,0,12">
                <ListItem>
                    <Paragraph>
                        <Bold>Slot rules</Bold> — item type condition + up to 4 top-priority affixes,
                        requiring any 2 of the 4 to match. Adjust the required count in the visual
                        editor to tune strictness.
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
                <ListItem>
                    <Paragraph>
                        <Bold>Target Uniques rule</Bold> — all unique items from the guide combined
                        into a single Specific Unique condition.
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
                <ListItem>
                    <Paragraph>
                        <Bold>All Charms rule</Bold> — a Talisman Set condition to show all charms,
                        added when the guide includes talisman/seal slots.
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
                <ListItem>
                    <Paragraph>
                        <Bold>Hide All fallback</Bold> — a catch-all hide rule at the end of the filter.
                    </Paragraph>
                </ListItem>
            </List>

            <Paragraph FontSize="14" FontWeight="SemiBold" Margin="0,8,0,6">
                Warnings
            </Paragraph>

            <Paragraph>
                If an affix or item name cannot be resolved to a known hash ID, it is reported as a
                warning rather than stopping the import. The rule is still created without the
                unresolved entry. Review warnings and add any missing conditions manually in the
                visual editor.
            </Paragraph>

            <Paragraph FontSize="14" FontWeight="SemiBold" Margin="0,8,0,6">
                Tuning the generated filter
            </Paragraph>

            <Paragraph>
                The generated filter is a starting point. After import, use the visual editor to:
            </Paragraph>

            <List Margin="8,4,0,12">
                <ListItem><Paragraph>Adjust the required affix count per slot (default: 2 of 4)</Paragraph></ListItem>
                <ListItem><Paragraph>Add or remove individual affixes</Paragraph></ListItem>
                <ListItem><Paragraph>Change rule colors to match your preferred highlight scheme</Paragraph></ListItem>
                <ListItem><Paragraph>Add item power or rarity conditions to further filter results</Paragraph></ListItem>
            </List>

        </FlowDocument>
    </FlowDocumentScrollViewer>

</UserControl>
